-- Venezuela Releases Four Econoinvest Brokerage Directors on Bail
-- B y   J o s e   O r o z c o
-- 2012-12-30T02:37:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-30/venezuela-releases-four-econoinvest-brokerage-directors-on-bail.html
Venezuela has released on bail four
directors of shuttered brokerage firm Econoinvest Casa de Bolsa
CA charged with illegal  currency trading .  Herman Sifontes, Juan Carlos Carvallo, Ernesto Rangel and
Miguel Osio, who had been in jail for two years and seven
months, have to report periodically to court and are banned from
leaving the country, the Globovision television network
reported, without saying where it got its information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jose Orozco in Caracas at 
 jorozco8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
